d 'TSADVROOT': module providing advanced time-series unit-root tests
d
d      tsadvroot is a library of modern univariate unit-root tests
d that go beyond the classical Dickey-Fuller framework in two	
d directions:	     1. Quantile-based testing. The qadf and fqadf
d subcommands test the unit-root hypothesis across the conditional
d quantiles	       of the series, so that persistence may
d differ in the lower, central and upper parts of the conditional
d distribution. 	   fqadf additionally allows smooth
d structural changes of unknown form through a flexible Fourier
d component.	    2. Structural breaks. The npadf subcommand
d allows two sharp breaks at unknown dates (in the level, or in the
d level and	       slope), and cisur implements the full
d Carrion-i-Silvestre, Kim and Perron (2009) battery of
d quasi-GLS-detrended tests	       with up to 3 estimated (or 5
d known) breaks, with critical values from the authors' response
d surfaces. 
d
d KW: time series
d KW: unit root
d KW: quantile
d KW: Fourier
d KW: structural breaks
d
d Requires: Stata version 14
d
d Distribution-Date: 20260708
d
d Author:   Merwan Roudane, NA
d Support: email  merwanroudane920@@gmail.com
d
f tsadvroot.ado
f tsadvroot.sthlp
f tsadvroot_cisur.sthlp
f tsadvroot_fqadf.sthlp
f tsadvroot_npadf.sthlp
f tsadvroot_qadf.sthlp
f tsadvroot_test.do
